	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="2" facs="R 6456-39 (81)"/>
			<p>The popular <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_romanians">Rumanian</term> reaction to the recent <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-345" type="subject">excesses committed against the Jews</term> is
				difficult of assessment. The <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_romanians">Rumanians</term> have heretofore insisted upon being known
				as a tolerant <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term>, and I do not doubt
				that the majority of them learn of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-540" type="subject"
					>massacres</term> and other <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-345" type="subject">atrocities</term>
				with, possibly, a slight feeling of satisfaction, mixed with a stronger sense of surprise, shock and misgiving. It is undoubtedly true
				that the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-342" type="subject">anti-Semitic campaign</term> of the
					<orgName ref="#ehri_dr_legionary_regime">Legionary régime</orgName>, the continual <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-341" type="subject">attacks of the press</term>, the present <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1076" type="subject">military</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-195" type="subject">collaboration</term> with <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-330" type="subject">anti-Semitic</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1152" type="subject">Germany</term>, and the attitude of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-948" type="subject">Government</term> during <persName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000010">General Antonescu’s</persName> absence at the front, during
				which time <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000706">Mr. Mihai Antonescu</persName> has been Acting
				Premier, have all had their effect on <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1072" type="subject">popular
					opinion</term>, tending to make it especially <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-342" type="subject"
					>anti-Semitic</term>, but I fail to believe that the country as a whole willingly countenances outright <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-345" type="subject">slaughter and brutality</term> in the handling of the
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-351" type="subject">Jewish problem</term>. [...]</p>
			<pb n="4" facs="R 6456-39 (83)"/>
			<p>But the fact remains that there has been no popular <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-212" type="subject"
					>uprising</term> or movement against all these <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-345" type="subject"
					>cruelties</term>. It may well be that the ethical sense of the <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_romanians">Rumanian</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1207" type="subject">people</term> has been somewhat dulled by recent
				miseries and disasters [...], with the result that they are not fully conscious of the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-345" type="subject">horrors of the Jewish phase</term>. Whatever the
				cause, 1941 has thus far proved to be a black year for the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-864"
					type="subject">Jews</term> in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798549/romania.html">Rumania</placeName>.</p>
			<p>My own experience is that the better class of <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_romanians">Rumanians</term> thoroughly disapproves of
				the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-337" type="subject">methods resorted to from time to time against
					the Jews</term>, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-345" type="subject">cruelty</term> and the
				injustice. [...]</p>
			<pb n="5" facs="R 6456-39 (84)"/>
			<p>The fact remains, however, that the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-901" type="subject">lower-class
					Jew</term> who has filtered into <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798549/romania.html">Rumania</placeName> since the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject">War</term> from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/562153/galicia.html">Galicia</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2017370/russian-federation.html">Russia</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/719819/hungary.html">Hungary</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/8505031/czechoslovakia.html">Czechoslovakia</placeName>, or elsewhere, and fastened upon village and
				small-town life is, by and large, not assimilable. The <term ref="#ehri_dr_nationalities_romanians">Rumanian</term> resents his
				presence, although it is largely due to his own laissez faire that this type of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jew</term> is here, and, from time to time when things
				are not going well, sporadic examples of appalling <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-345" type="subject"
					>cruelty</term> occur. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-896" type="subject">Jew</term> is always
				the convenient butt. Frank <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798549/romania.html">Rumanians</placeName> will admit that <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">robbery</term> is often the real leit motif.</p>
